### Instruction:
Who should not take Rylaze?

### Response:
RYLAZE is contraindicated in patients with a history of: 

• Serious hypersensitivity reactions to Erwinia asparaginase, including anaphylaxis [see Warnings 
and Precautions (5.1)]; 



• Serious pancreatitis during previous asparaginase therapy [see Warnings and Precautions (5.2)]; 
• Serious thrombosis during previous asparaginase therapy [see Warnings and Precautions (5.3)]; 
• Serious hemorrhagic events during previous asparaginase therapy [see Warnings and 
Precautions (5.4)].

